Pieter-Louis Myburg, News24(Felix Dlangamandla, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa's (Prasa) controversial contract for new locomotives has been reviewed and set aside by the High Court in Johannesburg."Harm will be done to the administration of justice if this award is not set aside from the onset. Corruption will triumph of this court does not set aside the tender," the court said in its judgment.The contract, awarded to little-known company Swifambo Rail Leasing in 2013, became mired in controversy after an expos&eacute; by Rapport newspaper which detailed the Afro 4000 locomotives' unsuitability for local rail lines. This is a developing story. Follow News24 for more details.BREAKING: South Gauteng High Court reviews and sets aside #Prasa "too tall" locomotives contract. Follow @news24 for more...&mdash; Pieter-Louis Myburgh (@PLMyburgh) July 3, 2017BREAKING: South Gauteng High Court reviews and sets aside #Prasa "too tall" locomotives contract. Follow @news24 for more...24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.